The paper deals with the complexity of the perfect matching problem in general graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The algorithmic techniques used in the paper are related to computational complexity theory, parallel algorithms, and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
